title: For Trade:  .50 Cal Pistol - Never Fired w/3 pound trigger pull.
postcontent: I have a .50 caliber percussion pistol. The half cock, full cock, works perfectly. The hammer is serrated for a better grip. The trigger pull is worked and as good as a modern gun. The trigger guard is brass, the rest of the metal is browned, instead of blued. Its fit and match on everything is perfect. This little 50 has not been fired yet. I have kept it in new shape for a long time. It is not a target pistol by any stretch, but would be a blast at a 7 yard indoor range! My thought originally was it was going to be my companion gun while out hunting with my 50 cal muzzleloader. Figured it could be my back up while out in the woods where muzzleloaders only are allowed. The stock is absolutely scratch and ding free and the browning has no wear, or marks at all in it. To hold it in your hand is very similar to holding a S&W Round Butt revolver. Barrel length is 5 inch. I've been out of shooting muzzleloaders for quite a while, so I'm looking to trade for something that I can shoot. I'm not looking for anything in particular, but I am taking any offers. The action on this gun is very impressive. I have had muzzleloaders that have had super hard trigger pull, to real bad creep, to sorry 1/2 cock/full cock workings. All I can say is it is a nice pistol with a real nice action and it would make a very shooter friendly 50 cal belt gun for someone who is looking for one. Mitch - 204-7560

title: For Sale:  LWRC M6A2 16" Patriot Brown Cerakoted FDE AR-15  .223 w/ Magpul PMAG not Colt Bushmaster Ruger
postcontent:
The M6A2™ rifle is a standard carbine available in various barrel lengths and in either 5.56mm NATO or 6.8mm SPC. The M6A2™ rifle is ideal for those who utilize optical sights as it employs a low- profile gas block. There is no A-frame front sight to obscure the field of view of the optical device. The M6A2™ rifle also features a longer midlength free float rail system with a removable return-to-zero top. Any M4 MIL Std 1913 accessory can be mounted to the rail, and because the rail has a monolithic profile, you can bridge devices from the receiver to the rail seamlessly. The longer rail also affords more 1913 “real estate” to mount your accessories.

The M6A2™ rifle can be used in various roles. With the 10.5 inch barrel, it is ideal for close quarters battle or fighting in built up areas. The 14.7 inch barrel M6A2™ rifle is an excellent general purpose carbine capable of effective fire out to 600 meters. And with the 16.1 inch barrel, the M6A2™ rifle can be used as a Squad Dedicated Marksman Rifle.

The M6A2™ rifle’s edge in capability, reliability, accuracy and long service life is the result of advanced technology materials and manufacturing processes, combined with progressive patented designs. All LWRCI™ carbine systems feature our short-stroke gas-piston operating system. The operating system is lightweight, self-regulating, and self-scraping. This system of operation does not foul the moving parts of the weapon with carbon or heat, greatly enhancing service life and reliability while decreasing both user and armorer maintenance. All M6A2™ rifles feature a match grade, cold rotary hammer forged barrel with a target crown. The barrel is treated with NiCorr™ surface conversion technology that extends service life, enhances accuracy, and increases the effective range of the weapon. As in all of our rifles, the bolt carrier group and the barrel extension of the M6A2™ rifle is coated with EXO’s patented nickel-boron surface conversion technology that provides a hard permanent lubrication to the moving parts.

title: For Sale:  NIB Benelli M4 Tactical 12ga
postcontent: Factory New Benelli M4 Tactical 12 gauge shotgun. Benelli has long been renowned for their world class sporting shotguns. Their attention to detail, craftsmanship and innovative recoil system make them some of the most desired guns on the market. In the early 90s Benelli released a "Tactical" version of their popular M1 Super 90 shotgun. While this gun was exceedingly light and functioned flawlessly in it's stock configuration it did have some short comings. During military evaluation of the M1 Super 90 it was determined that Benelli's standard Inertia system has cycling issues when large amount of weight (such as a night vision optic) was added to the system. Benelli's answer to this problem is the M4 Tactical. This shotgun utilizes their revolutionary A.R.G.O. short stroke gas piston system. This operating system employs 2 short stroke gas pistons as opposed to the 1 long stroke gas piston found in a typical Browning design.
